Version	 Comments                                                       By / Date
-------- --------                                                       ------------------

==========================================================================================
2.0.00	This is the initially versioned master copy of BaseSchema.		cnwdad1 14/02/2000

==========================================================================================
2.0.01	Updated with minor changes to CnEcHelpEntity classes.			cnwrdd1 29/03/2000

		Added fixes for the CnEcDesignTable's ColumnPictureArray		cnwdad1 29/03/2000
		property in the "buildTableColumns" and "updateThisRow"
		methods.

		Added the following methods to the FileNode class that are		cnwdad1 01/04/2000
		required by the "jhtSchema" framework:
			o cnEcFileExt.mth
			o cnEcFilePath.mth
			o cnEcFileStem.mth
			o cnEcUnqualName.mth

		Added the following method to String primitive:					cnwdad1 28/04/2000
			o cnEcConcat(pValue):String

==========================================================================================
2.0.02	Modified all External Function names to now have a prefix of	cnwdad1 09/05/2000
		"cnEc".

==========================================================================================
2.1.00	Upgraded to JADE 5.0.16.										cnwdad1 10/05/2000

		Modified CnEcUserInputForm:										cnwdad1 10/05/2000
			o TextBox's scrollHorizonal default changed to true
			o InstructionLabel's wordwrap default changed to true

		The the CnEcDesignTable now has the "selectedObjects" property	cnwdad1 11/05/2000
		protected and accessible via the "getSelectedObjects" method.
		Also modified the CnEcCollectionBrowserForm to use this method.

		Modified the CnEcDateBox where, when double-clicked to show		cnwdad1 12/05/2000
		the popup Calendar, that calendar will default to the current
		date entered in the Date Box.  Changes were made to:

			o CnEcCalendar
			o CnEcDateBox
			o CnEcCalendarForm

		Modified CnEcCalendar where, a double-click on a date (button)	cnwndl1	16/05/2000
		will select the date and close the form (equivalent to clicking
		on a date, then clicking the 'OK' button).

			o CnEcCalendar
			o CnEcCalendarTable

		Modified CnEcCalendar, where, when invoked from the CnEcDateBox	cnwndl1 16/05/2000
		control, it will be positioned next to the CnEcDateBox control,
		in similar fashion to some ActiveX dropdown calendar controls
		except that this will workout whether there is space on the
		screen to show the calendar next to the date control.  If there
		is insufficient space on the calling form to show the calendar,
		or if the portion of the calling form (of the invoking date
		control) is outside the desktop area, then the calendar control
		will be centered on the screen.

		Added a method called "CnEcSetColumnWidths" to the Table		cnwdad1 27/05/2000
		control.  Each column's width will be set as a percentage of
		the table's overall width.  The column's width percentages
		should be specified sequentially as subscripts of the
		"pColumnWidthArray" array.

		Added a new form called "CnEcMonitor", and added an application	cnwdad1 27/05/2000
		(called BaseSchemaMonitor) to run the form.  This form allows
		messages to be monitored.  The message can be coded into the
		logic by using the cnEcMonitor method on Object - when the
		method executes, the message will be sent to all copies of the
		Monitor applicaton.  The monitor can also be used to view
		JADE Nodes and Processes.

		Added String::cnEcEncrypt method. This is a one-way encryption	cnwdad1 31/05/2000
		method for strings.  This method was written because the
		CardSchema method returned characters that were invalid for
		XML messages over the internet.

		Added String::cnEcDecodeWebData. Query strings that are sent	cnwdad1 31/05/2000
		over the internet may contain hex values for some characters,
		for example each space will appear as "%20". This method will
		decode an entire query string and return a plain ASCII string.
		Note that when using JADE-enabled applications, such strings
		will automatically be decoded by the JADE Session class.

		Added the CnEcBaseRoot subclass of CnEcBaseEntity. This class	cnwdad1 01/06/2000
		will now be used to encapsulate any further collections of
		BaseSchema entities.

		Added CnEcHttp (subclass of CardSchema's CnHttp).				cnwdad1 01/06/2000

		Added CnEcWebTestEntity and its subclasses (see documentation).	cnwdad1 01/06/2000

		Added CnEcWebTestForm and its subclasses (see documentation).	cnwdad1 01/06/2000

		Added String::cnEcGetTagValueOfName primitive method to return	cnwdad1 07/06/2000
		the value of an HTML-type tag in the string.  For example, if
		the string had a value of "&lt;NAME&gt;Jack Frost&lt;/NAME&gt;", then
		calling this method with a parameter of "NAME" would return
		a value of "Jack Frost".

		Added Boolean::cnEcGetTableCheckBoxValue primitive method to	cnwdad1 08/06/2000
		return a String value suitable for setting the contents of a
		table control cell where the InputType for that cell is of
		type "Input_CheckBox".

		Added String::cnEcEncodeWebData primitive method to encode		cnwdad1 09/06/2000
		a string with web (HTTP) "special" characters.  For example,
		a space is represented in an HTTP string as %20%, therefore
		all spaces will be replaced with %20%.

		Added the String::cnEcSetHttpValueOfName and String::			cnwdad1 09/06/2000
		cnEcSetTagValueOfName primitive methods.  These methods
		will set the specified value for a query string field, or
		an HTML-type tag field, respectively within the string.
		
		Added the CnEcTcpConnection class.								cnwdad1 06/07/2000
		
		Added BaseSchema TTeach module.									cnwsmc1 10/07/2000
		
		Added the following methods to the Global class:				cnwdad1 02/08/2000
			o cnEcGetEnvironmentVariable
			o cnEcGetHttpBinary
			o cnEcGetHttpFile
			o cnEcGetHttpFileClient
			o cnEcGetHttpFileName
			o cnEcGetHttpFileServer
		
		Added the following three methods to the ListBox class:			cnwdad1 06/08/2000
			o cnEcFindParent
			o cnEcMoveSelected
			o cnEcMoveTree
			
		Added the following methods to the Global class:				cnwdad1 06/08/2000
			o cnEcConfirmDelete
			o cnEcGetAllPrinters
			o cnEcGetAllServerPrinters
			o cnEcGetServerTimeStamp
			o cnEcMessage_UnknownError
			
		Added the CnEcPrintFrame and CnEcPrintLabel custom controls.	cnwdad1 08/08/2000
		Also added the CnEcPrinter subclass of Printer.
			
		Added the BaseSchema Report Initiation module.					cnwdad1 11/08/2000

==========================================================================================
2.1.01	Added patches by cnwrdd1 for a parameter mismatch on the		cnwdad1 17/08/2000
		method BaseSchema::cnEcTeachDisplayTutorial.  Methods changed
		were:
			o app::cnEcTeachDisplayTutorial
			o ap::cnEcTeachLessonAvailable
			o CnEcTTeachMaintForm::keyUp
		
		Changed behaviour of CnEcCalendar control when the control was	cnwdad1 17/08/2000
		being created.  From JADE 5.1, the value of usage IO parameters
		are only copied back to the parameter of the calling method
		after the invoked method has finished executing and returns to
		the caller.  Thus, by creating the "monthTable" via the IO
		parameter of the "createTable" method, subsequent method calls
		by that method (which referenced the monthTable control) were
		causing 1090 exceptions.  Therefore, the method now explicity
		creates the monthTable control itself, and not from an IO
		parameter (this was unnecessary anyway, since the parameter was
		a reference on the calendar control).  This also required
		subsequent changes to the calendar control's "paint" method
		because, after the above change, when the control was loaded in
		the painter, it kept trying to rebuild itself in an eternal loop.
		Changed the paint method to detect if the control had already
		been built before trying to do so again.

==========================================================================================
2.2.01	Add the following method to the ListBox control:				cnwdad1 19/08/2000

			o cnEcRemoveSubItems(pParentIndex:Integer; pIsDeleteItemObjects:Boolean);
		
		This method will remove all listbox item entries from a
		list hierarchy that are beneath the item entry at the specified
		index position.  Optionally, any object that is set on the
		items's "itemObject property can also be deleted when the item
		is removed from the list.

		Added a constructor method to the CnEcAgent class to raise a	cnwdad1 19/08/2000
		"Base" exception (global.cnEcRaiseBaseException) if an attempt
		is made to instantiate a persistent instance of the class.
		
		Added the CnEcTable subclass of the Table control. This control	cnwdad1 20/08/2000
		will eventually be a replacement for the old CnEcDesignTable
		control.
		
		Added the following two constants to the Collection class:		cnwdad1 20/08/2000
		
			o CNEC_DISPLAY_ORDER_COLLECTION (Integer=0)
			o CNEC_DISPLAY_ORDER_REVERSED (Integer=1)
		
		These constants can be used when coding listCollection or
		displayCollection instructions.

		Modified the Class:cnEcDocumentSelf method.  Added the ability	cnwdad1 22/08/2000
		to also document Property Text, and prevented Jade RootSchema
		properties from being included.
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:					cnwdad1 22/08/2000
		
			o cnEcGetClassTreeName():String;
		
		This method returns a string with the name of the receiver's
		class hierarchy tree, in the format of a DOS filename.

		Added the following method to the Global class:					cnwdad1 22/08/2000
		
			o cnEcDocumentModel(pSchemaNameUpTo:String;
								pSchemaNameDownTo:String;
								pIncludeSource:Boolean;
								pIncludeRootSchemaClasses:Boolean;
								pBaseDirectory:String):String;

		This method generates HTML documentation files (using the
		Class::cnEcDocumentSelf method) for an entire class model.
		The files will be produced in a directory structure (beneath
		the starting base directory) that reflects the schema/class
		hierarchy.
		
		Modified the Global::cnEcGetReportParameterNames method to also	cnwdad1 22/08/2000
		find parameter name constants on superclass report form classes.
		
		Added patches to the CnEcDesignTable control to correct			cnwdad1 24/08/2000
		behavioural problems when setting column headings at run-time.
		These patches were specifically for the JADE Database Browser
		and the CnEcDisplayPanel control.

		Added the following method to the CnEcReportParameterSuper		cnwdad1 29/08/2000
		Form class:
		
			o isValidReportParameterNameLength(	pParameterName:String
										):Boolean updating, protected;
		
		This method will check that the name of a Report Parameter does
		not exceeed that maximum length that can be stored within JADE.
		Associated with this, the doValidateDetails method on the
		CnEcReportParameterForm was modified to call the above new
		method when validating a Report Parameter.
		
		Added the "pProgressPercent" parameter to the CnEcCsvFile::		cnwdad1 30/08/2000
		loadCsvFile method.  This will determine how frequently to
		refresh the progress bar by specifying a percent value, e.g.
		if the value is 10, then the progress bar will be refreshed
		with every 10 percent of the job that is completed.
		
		Changed the String::cnEcNextDelimitedField method; when			cnwdad1 30/08/2000
		checking if the "startPos" is less than the length of the
		receiver, also check whether it is EQUAL to the length of
		the receiver.
		
		Added the following method to the Binary primitive:				cnwdad1 04/09/2000
		
			o cnEcUnpackCString(pStartPos:Integer):Binary;
		
		This method Finds a C String and trims off the null
		terminated bit.  This is a reimplementation of the JADE
		"unpackCString" method which does not allow for unicode's
		two-byte characters.
		
		Modified the CnEcTcpConnection::cnEcDoReadCallBack method		cnwdad1 04/09/2000
		to convert the buffer contents from ANSI into Unicode if a
		Unicode version of JADE is running.
		
		Changed the CnEcTcpConnection::cnEcDoWebWriteBuffer method		cnwdad1 04/09/2000
		to convert the buffer contents from Unicode into ANSI if a
		Unicode version of JADE is running.
		
		Added the following new method to Global:						cnwdad1 28/09/2000
		
			cnEcIsValidHttpFile(pFilePathName:String;
								pIsIgnoreEmpty:Boolean;
								pErrorMessage:String output):Boolean;
		
		...to validate a (remote) file on an HTTP server.
		
		Changed the CnEcReportEditForm form when sorting the			cnwdad1 01/10/2000
		Parameters table control to use the "sortType" feature to
		sort column 1 numerically.  Also added sorting of column
		5 to the CnEcReportPrintStartForm form to also sort
		numerically.  This corrects a problem where, if there were
		&gt; 9 parameters, they were ordered as "1, 10, 2, 3..." etc.
		
		Added the following method to the Global class:					cnwdad1 11/10/2000
		
			cnEcGetAllFileNames(pFolder:FileFolder input;
								pFileNameArray:CnEcArray io;
								pIsIncludeSubdirectories:Boolean);
		
		...to return an array of all file names for the requested
		file directory (can optionally include subdirectories).
		
		Extended the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method to also			cnwdad1 11/10/2000
		generate an index HTML file for all of the class files
		that are generated.  Also, each class HTML document now
		includes a link back to the index file.  The links between
		the index and class files are relative to each other and
		can thus be moved to different disk locations whilst
		retaining the integrity of the hyperlinks.
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 12/10/2000
		
			o cnEcAsHtml():String;
		
		...to convert the receiver string into an HTML-compatible
		format.

		Added the following method to the Properties class:				cnwdad1 12/10/2000
		
			o cnEcDocumentSelf(pHtmlFile:File io;
							   pIsIncludeRootSchemaClasses:Boolean;
							   pSchemaColl:SchemaColl;
							   pPathToIndex:String);
		
		...to generate an HTML-format documentation.

		Added the following method to the Method class:					cnwdad1 12/10/2000
		
			o cnEcDocumentSelf(pHtmlFile:File io;
							   pIsIncludeSource:Boolean);
		
		...to generate an HTML-format documentation.

		Modified the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method (and its			cnwdad1 12/10/2000
		invoked methods on Class, Property and Method) to include
		a hyperlink on the documented property references of a
		Class back to the Class documentation file for the
		reference type.  For example, the "BaseSchema" (app) class
		has a reference named "myBaseRoot", of type "CnEcBaseRoot";
		the hyperlink in the documentation for this property would
		therefore link back to the HTML documentation file for the
		CnEcBaseRoot class.  Also modified the documentation of
		the Class text to convert the text string into an HTML-
		compatible string (such as rendering Carriage-Return and
		Line-Feed characters correctly in a web browser).
		
		Enhanced the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method (and its			cnwdad1 13/10/2000
		invoked methods on Class, CollClass, Property and Method)
		to include the Membership class for Collection classes,
		and to list the keys for Dictionary classes.
		
		Fixed a bug in the String::cnEcSubstringCount method where		cnwdad1 14/10/2000
		if the last found position of the string being counted was
		equal to the length of the receiver, the next iteration of
		the find would result in an index-out-of-range error.
		
		Modified the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method (and its			cnwdad1 14/10/2000
		invoked methods on Class, CollClass, Property and Method)
		to now generate three index files: Main, Index by Class
		Name, and Index by Hierarchy.
		
		Modified the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method (and its			cnwdad1 21/10/2000
		invoked methods on Class, CollClass, Property and Method)
		to now include a hyperlink to a collection's membership
		class back to its class documentaton file.
		
		Extended the Global::cnEcGetHttpBinary method to include		cnwdad1 25/10/2000
		a parameter to specify whether the operation should be
		server or client execution, and thus moved the guts of
		this method into another method that is called from either
		of two other methods explicity defined as client and server
		execution.  Also, to cater for multiple requests (method
		calls) simultaneously (thus requiring unique working file
		names), the network address of the requesting client is now
		used as the name of the temporary working file (of the
		fetched binary), unless no network address is available
		(such as when running in single-user mode, in which case
		the file name will be "working.dat").
		
		Changed the Global::cnEcFileException handler method to			cnwdad1 25/10/2000
		return a "pass back" value if the method (and hence the
		exception) is running on the server node, since a message
		box is neither valid nor sensible on the server node.
		
		Added the following methods to the Integer primitive:			cnwdad1 02/11/2000
		
			o cnEcDaysInMonth(pIsLeapYear:Boolean):Integer;
			o cnEcIsLeapYear():Boolean;
		
		The method names are self-explanatory.
		
		Added the following method to the Control class:				cnwdad1 02/11/2000
		
			o cnEcCopyFontSettings(pControl:Control) updating;
		
		...which will copy all of the font-related settings from
		the requesting parameter control to the receiver.
		
		Added the following method to the Printer class:				cnwdad1 04/11/2000
		
			o cnEcPrintToFitPage(	pPrinter:Printer input;
									pFrame:Frame input;
									pLabel:Label input;
									pTextWidth:Integer):Integer updating;

		This method will print the specified frame/label to fit
		the page.  For example, if a paragraph in the text is too
		large to fit on the (remainder of the) page, then the
		text will be printed upto the amount that can fit on the
		page, and the rest of the text will be printed on the
		next page, and so forth.
		
		Modified the "keyDown" and "scrollTable" methods on the			cnwdad1 06/11/2000
		CnEcDesignTable control to invoke the "scrolled" event
		after scrolling the table.  Also corrected a problem where,
		if the User attempted to scroll beyond the table's last row
		with the arrow keys, a 1090 exception was raised - the
		"scrollTable" method will now ignore such attempts if the
		control's iterator is not instantiated.
		
		Added the CnEcCalendarControl class (Custom Control) as a		cnwdad1 07/11/2000
		replacement for the old CnEcCalendar control (the old one
		is very inefficient and is occasionally corrupted on a
		Thin Client).
		
		Added the following new primitive methods:						cnwdad1 07/11/2000
		
			o Any::cnEcIsBetween(pLowCriteria:String; pHighCriteria:String):Boolean;
			o Any::cnEcIsGreaterThan(pCriteria:String):Boolean;
			o Any::cnEcIsGreaterThanOrEqual(pCriteria:String):Boolean;
			o Any::cnEcIsLessThan(pCriteria:String):Boolean;
			o Any::cnEcIsLessThanOrEqual(pCriteria:String):Boolean;
			o Date::cnEcAddMonths(pMonths:Integer):Date;
			o Date::cnEcAddYears(pYears:Integer):Date;
			o Date::cnEcDaysInMonth():Integer;
			o Date::cnEcGetAnsiFormat():String;
			o Date::cnEcIsBetween(pStartDate:Date; pEndDate:Date):Boolean;
			o Decimal::cnEcAsPercent(pDecimalPlaces:Integer; pIsRounded:Boolean):String;
			o Integer::cnEcDaysInMonth(pIsLeapYear:Boolean):Integer;
			o Integer::cnEcGetEasterSundayForYear():Date;
			o Integer::cnEcIsLeapYear():Boolean;
			o Real::cnEcAsMM():Real;
			o Real::cnEcAsPixels():Real;
			o String::cnEcGetAnsiDateFormat():Date;
			o String::cnEcGetAnsiTimeFormat():Time;
			o String::cnEcGetAnsiTimeStampFormat():TimeStamp;
			o String::cnEcIsNumeric():Boolean;
			o String::cnEcRemoveSubstring(pSubstring:String):String;
			o Time::cnEcGetAnsiFormat():String;
		
		Added the following new method to the Control class:			cnwdad1 07/11/2000
		
			o cnEcGetAccelerator():Character;
		
		This method returns the character after the first "&amp;" in
		the receiver control's caption.  If the receiver doesn't
		have a "caption" property, then a null value is returned.
		
		Added the CnEcCalendarSelectForm to replace the old				cnwdad1 08/11/2000
		CnEcCalendarForm, which is a pop-up calendar used as a
		date-picker, such as for the CnEcDateBox control.  This
		also now uses the new CnEcCalendarControl custom control
		instead of the old CnEcCalendar control.
		
		Modified the CnEcDateBox control to now use the new pop-up		cnwdad1 08/11/2000
		calendar form (CnEcCalendarSelectForm), which in turn now
		uses the new CnEcCalendarControl custom control.
		
		Added the following new primitive methods:						cnwdad1 08/11/2000
		
			o Decimal::cnEcRoundToFiveCents():Decimal;
			o String::cnEcGetArrayOfLines(pLineArray:CnEcArray io):Boolean;
			o String::cnEcGetNextLine(pStartPos:Integer io):String;
			o TimeStamp::cnEcSetDateAndTime(pDate:Date; pTime:Time) updating;
			o TimeStamp::cnEcIsLessThanOrEqual(pTimeStamp:TimeStamp):Boolean;
		
		Added patch to the CnEcVerticalSplitter custom control to		cnwrs2 14/11/2000
		handle a loss of focus in the "mouseDown" event.
		
		Added the CnEcHorizontalSplitter custom control.				cnwrs2 14/11/2000
		
		Added the following method to the Decimal primitive:			cnwdad1 15/11/2000
		
			o cnEcRoundToFiveCentsMod(pRemainder:Integer io):Decimal;
		
		This method is the same as the "cnEcRoundToFiveCents" method
		except that it also returns the discarded cents in the I/O
		parameter (pRemainder).
		
		Changed the CnEcReportAdminSuper::doCheckErrorStatus			cnwdad1 20/11/2000
		method's signature.  Changed the "pButton" parameter from
		type "Button" to type "Control" so that applications that
		reimplement (subclass) these forms can use JadeMask
		controls instead of Button controls.
		
		Added the Connection::cnEcGetStateDescription method to			cnwdad1 21/11/2000
		return a translatable string describing the current state
		of the connection.
		
		Changed the String::cnEcDecodeWebData method to check that		cnwdad1 21/11/2000
		each byte of the encoded character is a valid hex character
		before transforming it.  This is to allow for genuine
		percent characters in the data.
		
		Changed the Integer::cnEcDaysInMonth back to using a Binary		cnwdad1 22/11/2000
		array constant to determine the month from the receiver.
		
		Changed the CnEcDateBox control where the "date" property		cnwdad1 30/11/2000
		is set (from a cast string value) to use the Date primitive
		method "parseForCurrentLocale".  This is to handle any
		format of the (workstation) locale's dates.
		
		Added the following two methods to the Process class:			cnwdad1 01/12/2000
		
			o cnEcGetUserInfoFieldValue(pFieldName:String):String;
			o cnEcSetUserInfoFieldValue(pFieldName:String; pFieldValue):String;
		
		These methods can be used when storing delimited fields
		in the "userInfo" property of the Process object.
		
		Added the CnEcSplitContainer, a subclass of BaseControl.		cnwrs1 07/12/2000
		
		Added the following method to the Date primitive:				cnwdad1 19/12/2000
		
			o cnEcGetWeek():Integer;
		
		This method will return the week number of the year based
		upon the receiver.
		
		Added the following methods to the TextBox control class:		cnwdad1 20/12/2000
		
			o cnEcDate():Date;
			o cnEcDecimal():Decimal;
			o cnEcInteger():Integer;
			o cnEcReal():Real;
			o cnEcString():String;
			o cnEcTime():Time;
			o cnEcTimeStamp():TimeStamp;
		
		Changed the String::cnEcRemoveSubstring method to return		cnwdad1 20/12/2000
		a null value if the receiver is empty.
		
		Modified the String::cnEcFindReplace method with more			cnwdad1 01/01/2001
		efficient code.  Also changed the signature to the
		following:
		
			cnEcFindReplace(pScanFor:String; pReplaceWith:String; pIsFirstOnly:Boolean):String;
		
		The "pInString" parameter has been removed, and the method
		will now process the receiver string instead of the value
		of this parameter.  The method no longer returns a boolean
		value, but instead now returns the value of the receiver
		with the subsring(s) replaced.
		
		Modified the "doSelectRow" and "doSelectColumn" methods on		cnwdad1 03/01/2001
		the CnEcTable control to no longer clear currently selected
		cells so that multi-row/column selection is possible.
		
		Modified the signature of the CnEcXMLParser::extractTag			cnwdad1 04/01/2001
		method so that the pIdRef parameter is now simply "output"
		instead of "io".
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcTable control:			cnwdad1 05/01/2001
		
			o getFirstNonfixedRow():Integer;
		
		This method will return the number of the first non-fixed
		row in the table, or zero if there are no non-fixed rows.
		
		Added the following method to the ListBox control:				cnwdad1 08/01/2001
		
			o cnEcMoveAll(pTargetList:ListBox input) updating;
		
		This method moves all items from the receiver listbox into
		the target listbox specified by the input parameter.
		
		Added the following method to the Integer primitive:			cnwdad1 13/01/2001
		
			o cnEcGetDayName():String;
		
		This method will return a translatable string with the name
		of the day matching the value of the integer receiver.  If
		the receiver is &lt; 1 or &gt; 7, then a null value is returned.
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 19/01/2001
		
			o cnEcEncodeWebDataAndStripCrLf():String;
		
		This method is used to encode an HTTP string and strip out
		and Cr or Lf characters, all in the one go.  This saves
		having to process the string three times.
		
		Modified the CnEcTcpConnection::cnEcDoWebPostRequest			cnwdad1 19/01/2001
		method encode the HTTP string and strip out Cr and Lf
		characters all in one go to save processing time.
		
		Added the following two methods to the ComboBox &amp; ListBox		cnwdad1 25/01/2001
		Control classes:
		
			o cnEcSetObjectIndex(pTheObject:Object) updating;
			o cnEcSetTextIndex(pTextValue:String) updating;
		
		These methods can be used to set the listIndex value to
		the index of the specified value.
		
		Added the following method to the Table Control class:			cnwdad1 25/01/2001
		
			o cnEcSelectAllRows() updating;
		
		This method will set all rows in the receiver to selected.
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 25/01/2001
		
			o cnEcStripAtEnd(pMask:String):String updating;
		
		This method strips the mask from the receiver, but only if
		it is at the very end of the string, but not if self is
		entirely composed of the mask.
		
		Added the following new methods to the ListBox control			cnwdad1 25/01/2001
		class:
		
			o cnEcAddBranch(pText : String; pPosition : Integer):Integer;
			o cnEcAddLeaf(pText : String; pPosition : Integer):Integer;
			o cnEcFindWhere(pString : String; pParent : Integer) : Integer;
			o cnEcMoveAllTreesByName(pTargetList:ListBox input) updating;
			o cnEcMoveTreeByName(pTargetList:ListBox) updating;
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 29/01/2001
		
			o cnEcUnicodeToAnsi():Binary;
		
		This method is a temporary replacement for CardSchema's
		cnUnicodeToAnsi method that won't actually be publicly
		available until the release of CardSchema version 2.7.x.
		
		Added reimplementation of app.msgBox method.					cnwndl1 30/01/2001
		Under normal circumstances this simply inherits the standard
		app.msgBox method.  However if the 'flags' parameter is set
		to a negative value the form CnEcMsgBoxForm is called instead.
		The resultant dialog that is presented has the normal caption
		and message, but is presented with an OK button only, and will
		automatically close itself after (flags * -1) seconds if the 
		User has not already closed the Dialog by pressing OK.
		
		Added a new "displayValue" property to the 						cnwdad1 30/01/2001
		CnEcReportParameter class, of unlimited length.  This is to
		cater for very long descriptions of report parameters
		(previously, the parameter name was used, which has a length
		of 30 characters).
		
		Added the String::cnEcUrlEncode method to parse the data		cnwdad1 02/02/2001
		in 10k chunks to speed up the encoding of very large
		data strings.  The method also has the option of using
		either JADE or a DLL library to perform the encoding.
		Also changed the CnEcTcpConnection::cnEcDoWebPostRequest
		method to make use of the new String method.
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcTable conrol:				cnwdad1 04/02/2001
		
			o cnEcGetFirstNonFixedColumn():Integer;
		
		This method will return the number of the first non-fixed
		column in the table, or zero if there are no non-fixed columns.
		
		Added the following two custom controls (subclasses of			cnwdad1 05/02/2001
		the CnEcTextBox control):
		
			o CnEcScrollBox
			o CnEcTimeBox
		
		The CnEcScrollBox control automatically handles spinbox-style
		scrolling of integer values.  The CnEcTimeBox (a subclass of
		CnEcScrollBox) automatically handles the scrolling of a Time
		formatted by an option in the painter Properties.
		
		Added the BaseBackupApp application to perform a quiescent		cnwdad1 06/02/2001
		backup of the database.  This is a no-forms application
		that will terminate itself as soon as the backup is done.
		
		Added the following method to the Collection class:				cnwdad1 07/02/2001
		
			o cnEcIsNotEmpty():Boolean;
		
		This method is the opposite of JADE's "isEmpty" method,
		i.e. it will return a boolean flag to indicate whether the
		receiver collection is NOT empty.
		
		Added the CnEcSorter and CnEcSortKey classes.  These can		cnwdad1 08/02/2001
		be used for sorting primitive values.  Also added the
		following method to the Array class:
		
			o cnEcSort(pIsDescending:Boolean) updating, abstract;
		
		This method is reimplemented on the primitive array classes
		(e.g. StringArray) to automatically sort the receiver.  If
		the method is called for an array that is not of primitive
		membership then a 1216 exception will be raised.

==========================================================================================
2.2.02	Added the following method to the Object class:					cnwdad1 11/02/2001
		
			o cnEcGetSortValue():Any;
		
		This method is explicity for fetching the value of a
		CnEcSortKey instance.  Note that this is slightly slower
		than casting an Object to the CnEcSortKey class in your
		logic when iterating through the CnEcSorter.mySortColl.
		
		Added the following method to the Application class:			cnwdad1 11/02/2001
		
			o cnEcGetServerTimeStamp():TimeStamp serverExecution;
		
		This method will return a current TimeStamp value relative
		to the JADE database server node, for relative to the
		Application Server node if the Application Server is running
		in single-user mode.
		
		Added the following method to the Application class:			cnwdad1 11/02/2001
		
			o cnEcGetServerComputerName():String serverExecution;
		
		Returns the name of the computer on which the JADE database
		server node is running.
		
		Added the following method to the Application class:			cnwdad1 11/02/2001
		
			o cnEcNotImplemented();
		
		This method will display a dialog informing the User that the
		function they just tried is not yet implemented.
		
		Added the following abstract method to the Object class:		cnwdad1 17/02/2001
		
			o cnEcGetExtractString():String abstract;
		
		This is an abstract method.  Where necessary, it can be
		reimplemented to return a CSV formatted string of the object's
		property values.
		
		Added the CnEcReportLoader class.  By instantiating this		cnwdad1 17/02/2001
		class (as a transient), two methods are available:
		
			o extractReports():Boolean;
			o loadReports():Boolean;
		
		Both methods will ask for a file directory.  The extract will
		create two files, one for report defintions named "basereps.txt",
		and the other for the report parameters named "baserepparams.txt".
		The load method will also look for these file names.
		
		Added the following method to the FileNode class:				cnwdad1 18/02/2001
		
			o cnEcIsNotAvailable():Boolean;
		
		This method returns a boolean flag to indicate whether the
		receiver's filename is not available on disk.  This method is
		the opposite of the native "isAvailable" method.
		
		Added a property named "isRequired" to the CnEcTextBox			cnwka1 22/02/2001
		and CnEcDateBox controls.  This boolean property can be set
		either from the Properties dialog in the Painter, or from
		within developer code.  If true, then the textbox control
		will have a small red box painted in the upper-right corner
		of the control.
		
		Added the following methods:									cnwdad1 07/03/2001
		
			o Object::cnEcIsGUI():Boolean
			o Class::cnEcIsGUI():Boolean
			o Window::cnEcIsGUI():Boolean
		
		The methods will return a boolean flag to indicate whether
		the receiver is a GUI object/class.  The method on Object
		returns a false value, whilst the method on Window returns
		a true value.  The method on Class returns the value from
		the "inheritsFrom(Window)" method.
		
		Removed the CNEC_PRINT_ORIENTATION_IGNORED translatable			cnwdad1 08/03/2001
		string (this error has been removed from JADE).
		
		Added the following methods to the Object class:				cnwdad1 10/03/2001
		
			o cnEcGetPreviousMethods(pTheCallStack:ProcessStackArray io);
			o cnEcWritePreviousMethods();
		
		The cnEcGetPreviousMethods method will populate the pTheCallStack
		array with all method calls in the stack, but with itself and the
		calling method removed.  The cnEcWritePreviousMethods method will
		write the names of all methods in the call stack to the JADE
		Interpreter Output window.
		
		Added the following method to the Object class:					cnwdad1 14/03/2001
		
			o cnEcSortCollection(	pTheDynaDictionary:DynaDictionary io;
									pCollectionName:String;
									pAllSortKeys:CnEcSortKeyNameArray;
									pIsAllowDuplicates:Boolean);
		
		This method can be used to sort a collection attribute on the
		receiver object.
		
		Added back the XposeMap map file because the Xpose and			cnwdad1 15/03/2001
		CashBook applications have classes in their application
		schemas mapped to this file, and remapping their data is
		a rather sizable task.
		
		Extended the Object::cnEcSortCollection method to return		cnwdad1 15/03/2001
		a boolean flag indicating the success of the sort.
		
		Added the following method to the Collection class:				cnwdad1 15/03/2001
		
			o cnEcGetMemberType():Type;
		
		This method will return the Type of the receiver's membership.
		
		Added the following method to the Dictionary, ObjectSet			cnwdad1 15/03/2001
		and ObjectArray classes:
		
			o cnEcGetMemberClass():Class;
		
		This method will return the Class of the receiver's membership.
		
		Added the following forms for a Method Generator utility:		cnwndl1 06/03/2001
		
			o CnEcCodeGenBaseForm
			o CnEcMethodGeneratorForm
		
		These forms are used by the BaseMethodGenerator application
		in the BaseSchema.
		
		Added the following classes for an email facility:				cnwndl1 21/03/2001
		
			o CnEcEmailBaseForm
			o CnEcEmailAddressMaint
			o CnEcEmailAddresses
			o CnEcEmailAdmin
			o CnEcEmailBaseDataForm
			o CnEcEmailForm
		
		These ares can be used to send emails, maintain an Address Book,
		and to edit default information (i.e. sender address, mail server
		etc.)  Associated with this, the following entity classes were
		also added:
		
			o CnEcBaseEmailData
			o CnEcEmail
			o CnEcEmailAddress
			o CnEcEmailBaseData
			o CnEcEmailRoot
		
		Added the CnEcReportWriterReportArray class, whose				cnwdad1 26/03/2001
		membership is the JadeReportWriterReport class.
		
		Added the following method to the JadeReportWriterManager		cnwdad1 26/03/2001
		class:
		
			o cnEcGetAllReports(pAllReports:CnEcReportWriterReportArray io);
		
		This method will populate the pAllReports array parameter with
		every Report Writer Report object.
		
		Modified the XML utility to use metaschema methods because		cnwndl1 27/03/2001
		the XML application runs in the BaseSchema yet works with
		objects in subschemas - in this scenario, subschema copies
		of features return a 1010 exception (invalid context).
		
		As a result of this, the following methods have been removed
		from the BaseSchema:
		
			o Class::cnEcXmlNoid
			o Object::cnEcXmlNoid
			o Object::cnEcXmlFormat
			o Object::cnEcXmlImport
			o Object::cnEcXmlImportEpilog
			o Object::cnEcXmlTagIt
			o Object::cnEcXmlTagItLevel
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:					cnwdad1 29/03/2001
		
			o cnEcGetStringPropertyLength(pPropertyName : String) : Integer;
		
		This method will returns the length (in character units) of the
		requested string property.  It will return zero if the property
		doesn't exist, or if the property is not a string attribute.
		Unbounded slobs will return a negative length.
		
		Added the following BaseControl subclasses:						cnwndl1 30/03/2001
		
			o CnEcClock
			o CnEcClockAnalogue
			o CnEcClockDigital
		
		Changed the XML Utility application to separate the Hubble facility
		out from the XML Utility.  Hubble is now run separately, in the
		application schema where the data is to be loaded/unloaded, simply
		by instantiating the CnEcHubble form.
		
		Added the following IntegerArray subclass:						cnwdad1 31/03/2001
		
			o CnEcKeyCodeArray
		
		When this class is instantiated, it will automatically be populated
		with all key codes used by BaseSchema controls.  The developer can
		then add or remove any key code elements before sending the array
		to the Window::registerFormKeys method.

==========================================================================================
2.2.04	Fixed the CnEcXMLParser::stripComments method which was 		cnwdad1 04/04/2001
		causing an index out of bounds exception if the last tag in the
		XML message was a comment.
		
		Changed the String::cnEcValidateNZPhoneNumber method to			cnwdad1 09/04/2001
		also handle 027 and 029 mobile phone "Area" codes.
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:					cnwdad1 09/04/2001
		
			o cnEcGetBinaryPropertyLength(pPropertyName : String) : Integer;
		
		This method will returns the length (in character units) of the
		requested binary property.  It will return zero if the property
		doesn't exist, or if the property is not a binary attribute.
		Unbounded blobs will return a negative length.
		
		Added the following method to the File class:					cnwdad1 12/04/2001
		
			O cnEcIsNotEndOfFile():Boolean;
		
		This method returns a boolean flag to indicate whether the end
		of the receiver (file) has been reached.  This method is the
		opposite of the native "endOfFile" method.
		
		Added the following method to the Table control:				cnwdad1 16/04/2001
		
			o cnEcFindObjectRow(pTheObject:Object):Integer updating;
		
		This method searches the itemObject property values for each
		JadeTableRow in the table for the specified pTheObject parameter.
		If the specified object is found, then it's row number is returned.
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 17/04/2001
		
			o cnEcUpto(pMaxLength:Integer):String;
		
		This method will return the receiver (String) upto the specified
		maximum length.  If the specified length is zero, a null value
		will be returned.
		
		Removed the "protected" feature of the following methods:		cnwdad1 23/04/2001
		
			o CnEcCalendarControl::repositionAfterResize
			o CnEcCalendarControl::resizeContents
		
		Added the following method to the Real primitive:				cnwdad1 29/04/2001
		
			o cnEcConvertLength(pUnit : String; pTargetUnit : String) : Real;
		
		This method can be used to convert Real values of length between
		units of measure (e.g. from inches into centimeters.  Refer to
		the class constants on the primitive for units of measure that
		are handled.
		
		Renamed the following methods on the Integer Primitive:			cnwdad1 06/05/2001
		
			o cnEcIncrement as cnEcAdd
			o cnEcDecrement as cnEcTake
		
		Added the following methods to the Decimal Primitive:			cnwdad1 06/05/2001
		
			o cnEcAdd(pIncrement:Decimal):Decimal updating;
			o cnEcTake(pDecrement:Decimal):Decimal updating;

		Added the following methods to the Real Primitive:				cnwdad1 06/05/2001
		
			o cnEcAdd(pIncrement:Real):Real updating;
			o cnEcTake(pDecrement:Real):Real updating;
		
		Removed the "updating" option from the signature of the			cnwdad1 14/05/2001
		following method on the String primitive:
		
			o cnEcNextDelimitedField(pChar:String; pPos:Integer io):String;
		
		Modified the following method on CnEcTcpConnection:				cnwdad1 16/05/2001
		
			o cnEcDoWebGetRequest(pServer:String; pFilePath:String; pMessage:String; pTimeout:Integer; pResponse:String io):Boolean updating;
		
		The data in the pMessage parameter was not being sent to the
		destination server.
		
		Added the CnEcBaseException Global Constant category,			cnwdad1 16/05/2001
		removed the CNEC_BASE_EXCEPTION Global Constant, and removed
		the Exception Constant Category.
		
		Modified the following methods on the Any primitive:			cnwdad1 16/05/2001
		
			o cnEcIsGreaterThan(pCriteria:Any):Boolean;
			o cnEcIsGreaterThanOrEqual(pCriteria:Any):Boolean;
			o cnEcIsLessThan(pCriteria:Any):Boolean;
			o cnEcIsLessThanOrEqual(pCriteria:Any):Boolean;
		
		...these methods now also handles Binary, Character, Time,
		and TimeStamp values.  Also modified the signature so that
		the pCriteria parameters are all of Type "Any".
		
		Removed the following methods from the Global class:			cnwdad1 16/05/2001
		
			o cnEcRaiseBaseException(pErrorCode:Integer; pErrorMessage:String);
		
		Instead, exceptions are raised in the following following manner:
		
			CnEcBaseException.raise_(&lt;code&gt;, &lt;error&gt;);
		
		Implemented the following mapping method on the Exception		cnwdad1 16/05/2001
		class:
		
			o errorItem(set: Boolean; _value: String io) mapping;
		
		When setting the "errorItem" property, this method will ensure
		that the value does not exceed the maximum length by truncating
		the excess text.
		
		Changed the "getColumn" method on the CnEcAppGrid control		cnwdad1 20/05/2001
		so that if the control only has one column, then the method
		won't bother trying to calculate the column, but instead will
		simply return a value of "1".
		
		Changed the proportional height of the CnEcCalendarControl		cnwdad1 20/05/2001
		day name heading row.  If the calendar control is painted quite
		small, the text of the day heading names was too large for the
		row.
		
		Implemented the "mouseDown" event on the CnEcCalendarDay		cnwdad1 20/05/2001
		control, which invokes the same event on the CnEcCalendarControl
		control.  This enables developers to code for this event in their
		applications.

==========================================================================================
2.3.01	Added the following method to the Date primitive:				cnwdad1 24/05/2001
		
			o cnEcAddDays(pDays:Integer):Date;
		
		Added the following methods to the Time primitive:				cnwdad1 24/05/2001
		
			o cnEcAddHours(pHours:Integer):Time;
			o cnEcAddMinutes(pMinutes:Integer):Time;
			o cnEcAddSeconds(pSeconds:Integer):Time;
		
		Added the following methods to the TimeStamp primitive:			cnwdad1 24/05/2001
		
			o cnEcAddDays(pDays:Integer):TimeStamp;
			o cnEcAddHours(pHours:Integer):TimeStamp;
			o cnEcAddMinutes(pMinutes:Integer):TimeStamp;
			o cnEcAddMonths(pMonths:Integer):TimeStamp;
			o cnEcAddSeconds(pSeconds:Integer):TimeStamp;
			o cnEcAddYears(pYears:Integer):TimeStamp;
		
		Added the following new classes:								cnwdad1 24/05/2001
		
			CnEcDataValue (subclass of CnEcBaseEntity)
				CnEcCurrencyValue
				CnEcDate
				CnEcPhoneNumber
				CnEcTime
				CnEcTimestamp
				CnEcValueRange
					CnEcCurrencyRange
					CnEcDateRange
					CnEcDecimalRange
					CnEcIntegerRange
					CnEcTimeRange
					CnEcTimeStampRange
		
		These classes are intended to replace equivalent data values,
		with added features specific to the type of data being replaced
		(as per the "Replace Data Value With Object" refactoring).
		
		Added the following classes:									cnwndl1 24/05/2001
		
			CnEcMessageEntity (subclass of CnEcBaseCommunicationEntity)
				CnEcCreditCardMessage
					CnEcBuyLineManager
					CnEcBuyLineMessage
						CnEcBNZBuyLineAuthorisation
						CnEcBNZBuyLineBatchListing
						CnEcBNZBuyLineBatchTotals
						CnEcBNZBuyLineCompletion
						CnEcBNZBuyLineEnquiry
						CnEcBNZBuyLinePurchase
						CnEcBNZBuyLineRefund
						CnEcBNZBuyLineVoid
						
			CnEcBuyLineAgent (subclass of CnEcAgent)
			CnEcBuyLineMsgDict (subclass of MemberKeyDictionary)
			CnEcBNZBuyLineTcpConnection (subclass of CnEcTcpConnection)
			
			CnEcBuyLineBaseForm (subclass of CnEcBaseForm)
				CnEcBuyLineMessageForm
				CnEcBuyLineMgrMaintForm
	
		These class have been added for the interface to the BNZ Bank's
		BuyLine Credit Card Transaction processing service.

		Added the following new classes:								cnwdad1 27/05/2001
		
			CnEcUnitOfMeasure (subclass of CnEcDataValue)
				CnEcArea
				CnEcDensity
				CnEcEnergy
				CnEcLength
				CnEcLineDensity
				CnEcTemperature
				CnEcVolume
				CnEcWeight
		
		Fixed a bug in the CnEcCalendarControl::doCreateEvent			cnwdad1 28/05/2001
		method where the inherited "display" method was used instead
		of the methods "pDisplay" parameter.
		
		Change the CnEcDesignTable::copyToClipboard method to use		cnwdad1 30/05/2001
		the cnEcSetClipboardData call (external method) instead of the
		cnEcSetClipboardText call, which was inaccurately named.  The
		cnEcSetClipboardText external method was then removed.
		
		Added the following methods to the String primitive:			cnwdad1 30/05/2001
		
			o cnEcCopyFromClipboard() updating;
			o cnEcCopyToClipboard();
		
		The methods can be used to copy text from the Windows clipboard
		into the receiver, or to copy the receiver into the clipboard.
		
		Added the following methods to Global:							cnwdad1 31/05/2001
		
			o cnEcXHandlerDuplicate(pTheException:Exception):Integer;
			o cnEcXHandlerNoCollectionEntry(pTheException:Exception):Integer;
		
		These handlers can be used when adding an removing members of
		a collection in situations where an error may occur (such as
		a duplicate when adding, or a missing member when deleting),
		and where such errors can be ignored.

		Added the following new CnEcUnitOfMeasure subclasses:			cnwdad1 02/06/2001
		
			CnEcForce
			CnEcPower
			CnEcPressure
			CnEcSpeed
			CnEcSpreadRateByMass
			CnEcSpreadRateByVolume
			CnEcTorque
		
		Added the following methods to the Integer primitive:			cnwdad1 06/06/2001
		
			o cnEcGetHexColor():String;
			o cnEcGetRGBValues(pColorRed:Integer output; pColorGreen:Integer output; pColorBlue:Integer output);
			o cnEcSetColorFromRGB(pColorRed:Integer; pColorGreen:Integer; pColorBlue:Integer) updating;
		
		Added the CnEcColorArray class, a subclass of IntegerArray.		cnwdad1 06/06/2001
		
		Added the following new primitive Data Value subclasses:		cnwdad1 12/06/2001
		
			CnEcStringTransform (abstract)
				CnEcMetaphone
				CnEcSoundex
		
		Added the following new Dictionary/Spell Checkking classes:		cnwndl1 15/06/2001
		
			CnEcBaseSpelling
				CnEcSpellCheck
				CnEcSpellRoot
				CnEcSpellWord
			
			CnEcSpellCheckBaseForm
				CnEcSpellCheckForm
				CnEcSpellDictMaintForm
		
		Together, these classes and forms can be used to maintain a
		dictionary of words, against which text can be spell-checked.

==========================================================================================
2.3.01b	Added the CnEcString data value class, as a subclass of			cnwdad1 29/06/2001
		CnEcPrimitiveValue.
		
		Added the following classes:									cnwdad1 30/06/2001
		
			o CnEcSubstringArray (subclass of CnEcArray)
			o CnEcSubstringObject (subclass of CnEcArrayObject)
		
		These classes are used by the CnEcString class for returning an array
		of substrings.
		
		Fixed a bug in the CollClass.cnEcDocumentCollection method.		cnwdad1 05/07/2001
		Made a change to check whether the membership class was found
		(such where the membership is a primitive).  In such cases, the
		name of the Type will be used instead of the name of the
		membership class.

		Added the BaseDocModel application as a ready-made interface	cnwdad1 07/07/2001
		to the Global::cnEcDocumentModel method.
		
		Added a constructor to the CnEcCurrency class so that it will	cnwdad1 07/07/2001
		default the remote locale to the client's current locale, and
		default the exchange rate to "1".
		
		Added the following method to the Method class:					cnwdad1 08/07/2001
		
			o cnEcGetCallingMethod():Method;
		
		This method will return the calling method of the requestor.
		
		Added the following method to the GlobalConstant class:			cnwdad1 08/07/2001
		
			o cnEcGetCategory():ConstantCategory;
		
		This method will return the receivers global constant category.
		
		Changed the following two methods to return a boolean flag to	cnwdad1 16/07/2001
		indicate whether the HTTP field/Tag was found and set:
		
			String::cnEcSetHttpValueOfName(pName:String; pValue:String):Boolean updating;
			String::cnEcSetTagValueOfName(pName:String; pValue:String):Boolean updating;
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:				cnwrs1 19/07/2001
		
			o cnEcGetNextTagValueOfName(pName:String; pStartPos : Integer io):String;
		
		This method will scan the receiver for the value of an HTML-type tag,
		eg. "&lt;NAME&gt;value&lt;/NAME&gt;", starting from a specified position.
		
		Changed the String::cnEcGetTagValueOfName method to call the	cnwdad1 19/07/2001
		String::cnEcGetNextTagValueOfName method, starting from the first
		character of the receiver.
		
		Fixed XML data load screen to allow 60-character format names.	cnwndl1 23/07/2001
		
		Renamed the Table::cnEcFindObjectRow method to now be:			cnwdad1 04/08/2001
		
			Table::cnEcFindObjectRowNo
		
		Added the following methods to the Table class:					cnwdad1 04/08/2001
		
			o cnEcFindObjectCell(pValue:Object):JadeTableCell;
			o cnEcFindObjectColumn(pValue:Object):JadeTableColumn;
			o cnEcFindObjectRow(pValue:Object):JadeTableRow;
			o cnEcFindStringCell(pValue:String):JadeTableCell;
			o cnEcFindStringColumn(pValue:String):JadeTableColumn;
			o cnEcFindStringRow(pValue:String):JadeTableRow;
		
		Added the following method to the Integer primitive:				cnwdad1 10/08/2001
		
			o cnEcPadTrailingZeros(pLength:Integer):String;
		
		This method will pad the receiver with trailing zeros upto the requested
		length, and return the result as a string.  If the receiver is longer
		than the requested length, then it will be truncated to the requested
		length, and the result will be returned as a string.
		
		Added the following CnEcBaseEntity subclasses:						cnwrs1 10/08/2001
		
			CnEcReleaseEntity
				CnEcReleaseAgent
				CnEcReleaseController
				CnEcReleaseHistoryDetail
				CnEcReleaseHistoryMaster
				CnEcReleaseUpgrader
					BaseSchemaRelease
						BaseSchema_1_1_1
		
		Made the following changes to the CnEcTimeBox control:				cnwdad1 12/08/2001
		
			o Change the formatString options from format "0" and format "1", to format "1" and format "2".
			o When first added to a form, the formatString will default to format 1 (HH:mm).
			o Added two Class Constants for the formats, FORMAT_1 ("HH:mm"), and FORMAT_2 ("HH:mm:ss").
		
		Added the following methods to the MenuItem class:					cnwdad1 18/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetLevel():Integer;
			o cnEcHasSubmenu():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsSeparator():Boolean;
		
		The first method returns a boolean flag to indicate whether the receiver
		has any submenu items.  The second method will return a boolean flag to
		indicate whether the receiver is a menu separator.  Note that a Global
		Constant, named CNEC_MENU_SEPARATOR, was also added to the Literals
		Category, for use by this method.
		
		Added the following method to the Class class:						cnwdad1 18/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetObjectSize(pLength:Integer output; pBlobs:Integer output);
		
		This method will return the size (length) of the receiver, and the number
		of blobs found.
		
		Added the following method to the Date primitive:					cnwdad1 18/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetCentury():Integer;
		
		This method will return the century part of a date as 'nn', e.g. for a date
		of 16 Aug 2001, a value of '20' is returned.
		
		Added the following methods to the SchemaEntity class:				cnwdad1 18/08/2001
		
			o cnEcIsProtected():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsPublic():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsReadonly():Boolean;
		
		These methods will return a boolean flag to indicate the type of access
		to the receiver.  Also added to the Schema Entity class were the following
		Class Constants:
		
			o CNEC_ACCESS_PROTECTED (Character = "2")
			o CNEC_ACCESS_PUBLIC (Character = "0")
			o CNEC_ACCESS_READONLY (Character = "1")
		
		Added the following method to the Script class:						cnwdad1 18/08/2001
		
			o cnEcSetSource(pSource) updating;
		
		Added the following method to the File class:						cnwdad1 19/08/2001
		
			o cnEcSetFileName():Boolean updating;
		
		This method will prompt the user to select (or enter) a file name, and
		will then use that name to set the receiver's file name attribute.
		
		Modified the following two methods on CnEcSpellRoot:				cnwdad1 19/08/2001
		
			o bulkExport(pTheTargetOut:File input);
			o bulkLoad(pTheSourceFile:File) updating;
		
		Previously, these methods invoked an instance of CMDFileOpen to prompt the
		user for a file name.  This is now done from the methods' callers, using
		the File::cnEcSetFileName method, and the opened File object is now sent
		to these methods.
		
		Added the following classes:										cnwdad1 20/08/2001
		
			CnEcParser (abstract)
				CnEcArithmeticParser
		
		The CnEcArithmeticParser class, transient by default, can be used to
		evaluate arithmetical expressions.
		
		Modified the following String primitive method:						cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			o cnEcToStringArray(pAllTokens:StringArray io);
		
		This method used to create a String Array, then return it to the caller.
		The method now expects the array to be sent to it as a parameter.
		
		Renamed the StringArray::parseTokens method as StringArray::		cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		cnEcParseTokens.
		
		Added the following methods to fetch a Windows' child controls:		cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			Windows::cnEcGetAllChildControls(pAllChildControls:CnEcControlArray io) abstract;
				Control::cnEcGetAllChildControls(pAllChildControls:CnEcControlArray io);
				Form::cnEcGetAllChildControls(pAllChildControls:CnEcControlArray io);
		
		The Form implementation will return all of the form's controls.  The Control
		implementation will recursively scan only the receiver and it's children.
		
		Added the following method to the Integer Primitive:				cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			o cnEcAsWords(pTheFullLocale:LocaleFullInfo):String;
		
		This method will return the receiver expressed in words.  A null Locale
		will default to the client's current default locale.
		
		Added the following method to the Decimal Primitive:				cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			o cnEcAsWords(pTheFullLocale:LocaleFullInfo; pWordedWholeAmount:String io; pWordedDecimalAmount:String io);
		
		This method will return the receiver's whole and decimal values expressed
		in words.  A null Locale will default to the client's current default locale.

		Added the following method to the Real primitive:					cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			o cnEcAsWords(pTheFullLocale:LocaleFullInfo; pWordedWholeAmount:String io; pWordedDecimalAmount:String io);
		
		This method will return the receiver's whole and decimal values expressed
		in words.    A null Locale will default to the client's current default locale.
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcCurrency class:				cnwdad1 21/08/2001
		
			o amountInWords(pWholeUnits:String; pDecimalUnits:String):String;
		
		This method will return the receiver's amount value, expressed in words,
		and appended with the units of currency for the whole and decimal values
		respectively.
		
		Added the following method to the NumberFormat class:				cnwdad1 23/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetAllGroupings(pAllGroupings:IntegerArray input):Integer;
		
		Populates an array of integers that determine the number of digits in each
		group of numbers to the left of the decimal point.
		
		Added the following method to the Integer Primitive:				cnwdad1 25/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetGroupings(pTheNumberFormat:NumberFormat; pAllGroupings:StringArray io);
		
		This method populates the array parameter with groupings of the receiver
		based upon the size of the groupings that are appropriate for the locale.
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcProgressForm class:			cnwdad1 27/08/2001
		
			o resetCancelFlag() updating;
		
		This method will reset the form's cancelled flag back to false.
		
		Added a progress dialog to the CnEcSpellRoot's bulk load of			cnwdad1 27/08/2001
		dictionary words.  This also supports cancelling the load process.
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcCurrency class:				cnwdad1 30/08/2001
		
			o wholeAmountInWords(pWholeUnits:String; pDecimalUnits:String):String;
		
		Returns the receiver's currency amount, with the whole value expressed
		in words, and the decimal value expressed in digits.
		
		Added the following methods to the Date Primitive:					cnwdad1 30/08/2001
		
			o cnEcGetLastMonday():Date;
			o cnEcGetLastSunday():Date;
			o cnEcGetNextMonday():Date;
			o cnEcGetNextSunday():Date;
			o cnEcGetPreviousWeekDay():Date;
			o cnEcIsWeekDay():Boolean;
		
		Added enhancements to Hubble data loads.  Can now specify how 		cnwndl1 30/08/2001
		often to perform transaction commits, and collection properties are
		now fetch once per class instead of for every instance of the class.
==========================================================================================
2.4.01	Added the following method to the CnEcProgressForm class:			cnwdad1 02/09/2001
		
			o checkCancelFlag():Boolean;
		
		This method will ask the user to confirm the cancel.  If the user does confirm
		the cancel, then this method will automatically unload the progress dialog form.
		If the user chooses not to confirm the cancel, then this method will reset the
		isCancelled flag back to false.
		
		Added the following method to the Object class:						cnwdad1 08/09/2001
		
			o cnEcIsNotTransient():Boolean;
		
		This method will return a boolean flag to indicate whether the reciever
		is NOT a transient object.  THis is th eopposite to JADE's "isTransient".
		
		Changed CnEcBaseException into an abstract class, and added the		cnwdad1 08/09/2001
		following subclasses of CnEcBaseException:
		
			CnEcBaseSchemaException
			CnEcBaseXmlException
		
		Also removed the CnEcXmlException class (replaced by CnEcBaseXmlException).
		Additionally, pushed the Exception::errorItem mapping method down onto the
		CnEcBaseException class.
		
		Pulled the CnEcReportParameterValueForm::doBrowse method up to the	cnwdad1 14/09/2001
		CnEcReportParameterValueSuper class.  This will enable developers to
		reimplement the method on the CnEcReportParameterValueForm class in
		their application schema, without having to subclass the form first.
		
		Added the following External Function:								cnwdad1 28/09/2001
		
			o cnEcGetKeyState(pVirtualKeyCode:Integer):Integer is GetKeyState in user32;
		
		This method returns the state of the requested key (determined by the
		pVirtualKeyCode parameter) as at the time the last processed keyboard
		message was generated.  A value of "1" indicates that the key is "on".

==========================================================================================
2.5.01	Added the following method to the Window class:						cnwdad1 06/10/2001

			o cnEcPrintMe() updating, protected;
		
		This method will print the receiver on the client's default printer.
		
		Added the following method to the Table class:						cnwdad1 06/10/2001
		
			o cnEcGetRowObject():Object;
		
		This method will return the object of the JadeTableRow for the currently
		selected row in the table.
		
		Added the following methods to the CnEcComboBox class:				cnwdad1 07/10/2001
		
			o getItemValueBinary(pItemIndex:Integer):Binary;
			o getItemValueString(pItemIndex:Integer):String;
			o setItemValueBinary(pItemIndex:Integer; pValue:Binary);
			o setItemValueString(pItemIndex:Integer; pValue:String);
		
		These method allow either a binary or string value to be stored for each
		entry in the combobox control.  The values may be of any length.
		
		Added the following methods to the Label control class:				cnwdad1 08/10/2001
		
			o cnEcDate():Date;
			o cnEcDecimal():Decimal;
			o cnEcInteger():Integer;
			o cnEcReal():Real;
			o cnEcString():String;
			o cnEcTime():Time;
			o cnEcTimeStamp():TimeStamp;
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcStringTransform class:		cnwdad1 26/10/2001
		
			o getTransform(pMaxLength : Integer):String abstract;
		
		This abstraction is reimplemented on the CnEcMetaphone and CnEcSoundex
		classes, which replace the getMetaphoneValue() and getSoundexValue
		methods respectively.
		
		Added the following Data Value classes:								cnwdad1 29/10/2001
		
			CnEcFinancialValue (abstract)
				CnEcAmortize
		
		The CnEcAmortize class can be used to calculate a load amortization.
		
		Added the following development-time property to the CnEcTextBox	cnwdad1 31/10/2001
		
			o isReadOnlyDefaultColor (Boolean)
		
		By default, when the CnEcTextBox control is set to read-only, its background
		color changes to that of a 3D face, i.e. to give the appearance of a 3D Label
		control.  After setting the above property to true, no attempt will be made to
		change the background color when the read-only property is set, thus allowing
		the developer to set an alternative background color.
		
		Added the following methods to the Object class:					cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o cnEcInspect();
			o cnEcInspectModal();
		
		These methods will invoke the BaseSchema Inspector for the receiver object.
		
		Added the following method to the NumberFormat class:				cnwdad1 01/11/201
		
			o cnEcStripNonNumeric(pValue:String):String;
		
		Strips all non-numeric characters from the specified value, and returns
		the result.
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:					cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o cnEcAsNumeric(pTheNumberFormat:NumberFormat):String;
		
		Using the current Locale's numeric information, strips all non-numeric
		characters and returns the result.
		
		Added the following Custom Controls:								cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o CnEcCurrencyLabel
			o CnEcCurrencyBox
			o CnEcNumericLabel
			o CnEcNumericBox
		
		Added the following method the CnEcLabel control:					cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o cnEcSetPositiveValueColor(pIsPositive : Boolean) updating;
		
		This method will set the foreColor property of the control to either black
		or red, depending upon whether the (numeric) value of the caption is
		positive or negative.
		
		Added the following methods to the SchemaEntity classes:			cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o Feature::cnEcIsProperty():Boolean
				o Property::cnEcIsAttribute():Boolean;
				o Property::cnEcIsCollection():Boolean;
				o Property::cnEcIsPrimitive():Boolean;
				o Property::cnEcIsPrimitiveArray():Boolean;
				o Property::::cnEcIsProperty():Boolean
				o Property::cnEcIsReference():Boolean;
					o Attribute::cnEcIsAttribute() : Boolean;
						o CompAttribute::cnEcIsPrimitiveArray() : Boolean;
						o PrimAttribute::cnEcIsPrimitive() : Boolean;
					o Reference::cnEcIsReference(): Boolean;
			o Type::cnEcIsCollection():Boolean;
			o Type::cnEcIsPri) : Boolean;
				o PrimType::cnEcIsPrimitive() : Boolean;
		
		Unprotected the following method on the CollClass class:			cnwdad1 01/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetCollectionTypeName():String;
		
		Added the following Global Constants to the CnEc_Keycode_Extras		cnwdad1 03/11/2001
		category:
		
			o CNEC_KEY_F12 (Integer, value=123)
			o CNEC_KEY_F8 (Integer, value=119)
			o CNEC_KEY_F9 (Integer, value=120)
		
		Added the CnEcObjectInspectorForm, which can be invoked by either	cnwdad1 04/11/2001
		of the following two methods on the Object class:
		
			o cnEcInspect();
			o cnEcInspectModal();
		
		Calling either of these methods at run-time will invoke the BaseSchema
		Inspector form, which is an enhanced version of the native inspector
		for interrogating the receiver.
		
		Moved the parsing of numbers into words from the Integer primitive	cnwdad1 05/11/2001
		onto the Real primitive to handle larger numbers (upto Billiards/Quadrillions).
		Also addd the following method to the Real primitive:
		
			o cnEcAsWordsWhole(pTheFullLocale:LocaleFullInfo):String;
		
		This method will parse a single whole value only.  The Integer and Decimal
		methods will now use this method to parse their constituent parts (or the
		whole value in the case of Integer values).
		
		Removed the following method from the Integer primitive:			cnwdad1 05/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetGroupings(pTheNumberFormat:NumberFormat; pAllGroupings:StringArray io);
		
		Added the following method to the String primitive:					cnwdad1 05/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetNumberGroupings(pTheNumberFormat:NumberFormat; pAllGroupings:StringArray io);
		
		Added the following methods to the String primitive:				cnwdad1 14/11/2001
		
			o cnEcPadLeading(pPadLength:Integer; pPadCharacter:Character):String;
			o cnEcPadTrailing(pPadLength:Integer; pPadCharacter:Character):String;
		
		These methods will pad the beginning and end of the receiver (respectively)
		to the requested length, with the specified character.  If the length of the
		receiver is equal-to or greater than the requested length, then it will be
		returned unchanged.
		
		Removed the following method from the String primitive:				cnwdad1 14/11/2001
		
			o cnEcUnicodeToAnsi() : Binary;
		
		This method was a temporary filler for the CardSchema equivalent, which wasn't
		available until the 2.7.x CardSchema release.
		
		Added a check to the CnEcPhoneNumber::validateForNZ method to		cnwdad1 14/11/2001
		report a phone number as valid if it's null.
		
		Added the following method to the Window class:						cnwdad1 18/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetRelativePosition(pTheWindow:Window input; pXposition:Real io; pYposition:Real io) updating;
		
		This method will update the X-Y coordinates of the specified window relative
		to the screen.  This can be used, for example, when invoking a popup menu
		from a control that is a child of another control.  JADE assumes that a menu's
		coordinates are relative to the Window, but if the menu is invoked from a child
		control, the X-Y coordinates are actually relative to the coordinates of the
		control's parent control.  This method will convert the child control's
		coordinates relative to the Window.
		
		Added support for the following events to the CnEcDesignTable		cnwdad1 19/11/2001
		control: arrow key up, arrow key down, page up and page down.  When these
		keys are pressed, the table will be scrolled and the click() event for the
		new row will be invoked, effectively simulating a scroll with either the
		scroll bar or by selecting a new row by clicking on it with the mouse.
		
		Added the following method to the GBaseSchema (Global) class:		cnwdad1 19/11/2001
		
			o cnEcReadBinaryFile(pFileName:String):Binary;
		
		This method will read a file from disk as binary data.
		
		Renamed the File::cnEcSetFileName() method as cnEcSetOpenName().	cnwdad1 19/11/2001
		
		Added the following method to the File class:						cnwdad1 19/11/2001
		
			o cnEcSetSaveName(pDefaultName:String; pCreatePrompt:Boolean; pOverwritePrompt:Boolean):Boolean updating;
		
		This method will prompt the user to select (or enter) a file name,
		and will then use that name to set the receiver's file name.
		
		Added the following method to the GBaseSchema (Global) class:		cnwdad1 20/11/2001
		
			o cnEcConfirmAction(pActionName:String; pEntityName:String):Boolean;
		
		Returns a flag after asking the User for confirmation of an action.
		
		Added the "isRequired" property to the following controls:			cnwdad1 22/11/2001
		
			o CnEcComboBox
			o CnEcListBox
			o CnEcTable
		
		This property can be set at either development-time (in the Properties dialog
		of the Painter) or at run-time.  When set to true, a small red box will be
		painted in the top-right corner of the control to indicate to the user that
		a value or selected is required by the application.
		
		Modified the "windowCreated" event method on the following			cnwdad1 22/11/2001
		controls:
		
			o CnEcComboBox
			o CnEcDateBox
			o CnEcListBox
			o CnEcTable
			o CnEcTextBox
		
		The method will check for the "isRequired" proeprty, and paints a red box in the
		top-right corner of the control if necessary.  Previously this was ignored within
		the Painter - it will now paint the box within the Painter as well.
		
		Added the following CnEcBaseEntity subclasses to support HTML Tags:	cnwdad1 24/11/2001
		
			o CnEcHtmlObject
				o CnEcHtmlTagObject
					o CnEcHtmlTableObject
						o CnEcHtmlTableTag
						o CnEcHtmlTableDataTag
						CnEcHtmlTableRowTag
					o CnEcHtmlAnchorTag
					o CnEcHtmlFontTag
					o CnEcHtmlImageTag
					o CnEcHtmlInputTag
					o CnEcHtmlOptionTag
					o CnEcHtmlSelectTag
		
		These classes, which are transient by default, can be populated with data and settings
		to generate HTML code.
		
		Added the "CnEcHex_Colors" Global Constant category.  The values	cnwdad1 24/11/2001
		the constants in this category can be used to set a variety of colors in
		HTML code.
		
		Added the following method to the ListBox control:					cnwdad1 24/11/2001
		
			o cnEcOpenDownTo(pListIndex:Integer);
		
		This method will open the receiver's tree nodes to reveal the node at the
		specified item index.
		
		Added the following External Functions to the kernel32 library:		cnwdad1 27/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetDiskFreeSpaceExA(pPath:String [256]; pUserFreeBytesAvailable:Binary[8] io; pTotalNumberOfBytes:Binary[8] io; pTotalNumberOfFreeBytes:Binary[8] io) is GetDiskFreeSpaceExA in kernel32;
			o cnEcGetDiskFreeSpaceExW(pPath:String[256]; pUserFreeBytesAvailable:Binary[8] io; pTotalNumberOfBytes:Binary[8] io; pTotalNumberOfFreeBytes:Binary[8] io) is GetDiskFreeSpaceExW in kernel32;
			o cnEcGlobalMemoryStatus(pStatusStructure : Binary[256] io) is GlobalMemoryStatus in kernel32;
		
		The functions are used to extract available resource information from the target computer.
		
		Added the following method to the Global (GBaseSchema) class:		cnwdad1 27/11/2001
		
			o cnEcXHandlerResumeNext(pTheExceptionObject:Exception; pErrorNumber:Integer output; pErrorText:String output):Integer;
		
		Exception handler to passes control back to the method that armedthis handler. 
		Execution will resume from the next expression after the evaluation of the
		method call or expression in which the exception occurred.
		
		Added the following method to the Node class:						cnwdad1 27/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetTotalAndAvailableMemory(pTotalMemory:Integer output; pAvailableMemory:Integer output);
		
		Returns the node workstation's total and available memory.  If the method is
		called from a Thin Client, then the values returned will be from the Application
		Server's node.
		
		Added the following methods to the System class:					cnwdad1 27/11/2001
		
			o cnEcGetServerDiskAndMemory(pFreeMemory:Integer output; pFreeDiskSpace:Decimal output; pDriveName:String output) serverExecution;
			o cnEcGetServerNameAndMemory(pMachineName:String output; pTotalMemory:Integer output) serverExecution;
		
		The first of these methods will return the free memory, disk space and the drive
		name (letter) from the database server node's machine.  The second method will
		return the machine name and total memory from the database server node's machine.
		
		Added the CnEcRulerBar Picture control subclass.					cnwdad1 03/12/2001
		
		Fixed the CnEcCalendarControl::setMinValue method to default the	cnwdad1 04/12/2001
		maximum value to the minimum value if the new minimum value is greater than
		the old maximum value.
		
		Changed the Calendar Select form to use a Scroll Box for the Year	cnwdad1 04/12/2001
		instead of a native spinbox, thus allowing the year to be scrolled between
		the years 1 and 9999 - previously, the year could only be scrolled 20 years
		either side of the current year.
		
		Added the following method to the CnEcCheckProse class:				cnwdad1 09/12/2001
		
			o isCheckProse(pProse:String; pCheckedProse:String output):Boolean updating;
		
		This method will check the specified prose, and return the updated string. The
		method will return True if the prose was updated, otherwise it will return false.
		The checked prose is always returned in the output pCheckedProse parameter,
		regardless of whether it was updated or not.
		
		Added the following method to the TextBox control:					cnwdad1 09/12/2001
		
			o cnEcDoSpellCheck():Boolean updating;
		
		This method will Spell-Check the receiver's text, and update it if the prose has
		been modified.  The method will return a value of true if the text was changed,
		otherwise it will return a false value.
		
		Added the following classes:										cnwndl1 19/12/2001
		
			CnEcBackShedBase (abstract)
				CnEcBackShedManager
				CnEcBackShedTask (abstract)
			
			CnEcBaseTaskForm
				CnEcTaskDetailsForm
				CnEcTaskManagerForm
				CnEcTaskMonitorForm
		
		These classes are used for the BaseSchema background task scheduler.
		
		Added the following classes:										cnwdad1 24/12/2001
		
			CnEcLocaleEntity (abstract)
				CnEcLocaleFormat (abstract)
					CnEcDateFormat
					CnEcNumberFormat
						CnEcCurrencyFormat
					CnEcTimeFormat
				CnEcLocaleInfo
		
		These classes can be used to persist locale and format information.
		
		Added the following properties to the CnEcDataValue class:			cnwdad1 24/12/2001
		
			o myLocaleInfo (Kind = CnEcLocaleInfo)
			o myRemoteLocaleInfo (Kind = CnEcLocaleInfo)
		
		These properties replace what were previously references to the native
		LocaleFullInfo class.
		
		Added the following methods to the CnEcDisplayPanel class:			cnwdad1 02/01/2002
		
			o clearDisplay();
			o refreshSelectedRow() updating;
		
		These methods will clear the display panel details, and refresh the display
		panel details for the currently selected row in he data table, respectively.
		
		Reimplemented the following methods which are inherited from the	cnwdad1 03/01/2002
		TextBox control:
		
			o cnEcDate():Date;
			o cnEcDecimal():Decimal;
			o cnEcInteger():Integer;
			o cnEcReal():Real;
			o cnEcString():String;
			o cnEcTime():Time;
			o cnEcTimeStamp():TimeStamp;
		
		These methods will now return appropriate values within the context of the
		control.  For example, the CnEcDateBox will return null for the cnEcTime()
		method, the CnEcNumericBox will assume a Julian day number for cnEcDate(),
		and will assume a number of milliseconds since midnight for cnEcTime(), etc.
		
		Added the following methods to the System class:					cnwdad1 05/01/2002
		
			o cnEcIsCapsLock():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsNumLock():Boolean;
			o cnEcIsScrollLock():Boolean;
		
		These methods will return a boolean flag to indicate whether the keyboard's
		Caps, Num or Scroll Lock, respectively, is currently on.
		
