==========================================================================================
2.5.02	Added the following External Functions to the Kernel32 library:		cnwdad1 17/01/2002
		
			o cnEcCopyFile(pSourceFile:String; pTargetFile:String; pIsFailIfExists:Boolean):Integer is CopyFileA in kernel32;
			o cnEcCreateDirectory(pPathName:String; pSecurityAttributes:String):Integer is CreateDirectoryA in kernel32;
			o cnEcCreateFile(pFileName:String; pAccessMode:Integer; pShareMode:Integer; pSecurityAttributes:String; pCreateDisposition:Integer; pFileAttributes:String; pTemplateHandle:Integer):Integer is CreateFileA in kernel32;
			o cnEcMoveFile(pSourceFile:String; pTargetFile:String):Integer is MoveFileA in kernel32;
			o cnEcRemoveDirectory(pPathName:String):Integer is RemoveDirectoryA in kernel32;
		
		Added the abstract FileNode::cnEcGetAttributes method.				cnwdad1 18/01/2002
		
		Changed the signature of the cnEcGetFileAttributes External			cnwdad1 18/01/2002
		Function of the Kernel32 library to:
		
			o cnEcGetFileAttributes(pNodeName:String):Integer is GetFileAttributesA in kernel32;
		
		Added the following abstract methods to the FileNode class, which 	cnwdad1 18/01/2002
		are implemented on the File and FileFolder classes:
		
			o cnEcCopy(pTarget:String):Boolean updating, abstract;
			o cnEcMove(pTarget:String):Boolean updating, abstract;
			o cnEcRemove() : Boolean updating, abstract;
		
		Fixed the Object::cnEcSortCollection method.  Previously the		cnwdad1 20/01/2002
		method was checking whether the receiver object was a Dictionary Type.  Changed this
		to now check whether the property to be sorted is a collection.
		
		Removed the following methods from the Object class:				cnwdad1 20/01/2002
		
			o cnEcTransactionBegin
			o cnEcTransactionCommit
		
		Added the following method to the Integer primitive:				cnwdad1 20/01/2002
		
			o cnEcNumberFormat():Integer;
		
		This method will return the receiver, formatted as a string.  For example, 1234 will
		be returned as "1,234" (the native equivalent of this method returns the receiver
		as a decimalized value).
		
		Added the following methods to the Decimal primitive:				cnwdad1 20/01/2002
		
			o cnEcNumberFormat():Integer;
			o cnEcFractionValue():Integer;
			o cnEcWholeValue():Integer;
		
		The cnEcNumberFormat method will return the receiver, formatted as a string.  For example,
		1234.56 will be returned as "1,234.56".  The cnEcFractionValue and cnEcWholeValue methods
		will return the receiver's fractional part and whole part as an integer value respectively.
		
		Added the following Primitive methods:								cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		
			o Decimal::cnEcAsKilobytes():Real;
			o Decimal::cnEcAsMegabytes():Real;
			o Integer::cnEcAsKilobytes():Real;
			o Integer::cnEcAsMegabytes():Real;
			o Real::cnEcAsKilobytes():Real;
			o Real::cnEcAsMegabytes():Real;
		
		These methods will convert the receiver's value into the kilobyte or megabyte equivalent.
		
		Added the following External Functions to the advapi32 library:		cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		
			o cnEcRegCloseKey(hKey : Integer) : Integer is RegCloseKey in advapi32;
			o cnEcRegOpenKeyA(hKey:Integer; sKey:String[256]; result:Integer output):Integer is RegOpenKeyA in advapi32;
			o cnEcRegOpenKeyW(hKey:Integer; sKey:String[256]; result:Integer output):Integer is RegOpenKeyW in advapi32;
			o cnEcRegQueryValueExA(hKey:Integer; sKey:String[256] io; reserved:Integer; type:Integer; data:Binary[256] io; length:Integer io):Integer is RegQueryValueExA in advapi32;
			o cnEcWinRegQueryValueExW(hKey:Integer; sKey:String[256] io; reserved:Integer; type:Integer; data:Binary[256] io; length:Integer io):Integer is RegQueryValueExW in advapi32;
			o cnEcRegQueryValueExW(hKey:Integer; sKey:String[256] io; reserved:Integer; type:Integer; data:Binary[256] io; length:Integer io):Integer is RegQueryValueExW in advapi32;
		
		Added the following External Functions to the kernel32 library:		cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		
			o cnEcGetSystemInfo(pSystemData : Binary[36] io) is GetSystemInfo in kernel32;
		
		Added the following methods to the System class:					cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		
			o cnEcGetCPUInfo():String;
			o cnEcGetDiskAndMemory(pFreeMemory:Integer output; pFreeDiskSpace:Decimal output; pDriveName:String output);
			o cnEcGetNameAndMemory(pMachineName:String output; pTotalMemory:Integer output);
			o cnEcGetServerCPUInfo():String serverExecution;
		
		Renamed the Node::cnEcGetTotalAndAvailableMemory method to Node::	cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		cnEcGetMemory.  Also added the following new method to Node:
		
			o cnEcGetServerMemory(pTotalMemory:Integer output; pAvailableMemory:Integer output) serverExecution;
		
		This is a server-execution version of the Node::cnEcGetMemory method.
		
		Renamed the cnEcCopyFile External Function as cnEcCopyFileA, and	cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		added a new function called cnEcCopyFileW.
		
		Renamed the cnEcGetCommandLine External Function as					cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		cnEcGetCommandLineA, and added a new function called cnEcGetCommandLineW.
		
		Changed the Global::cnEcGetCommandLineParameter method to check		cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		for Unicode, and to call the appropriate External Function.
		
		Renamed the cnEcCreateDirectory External Function as				cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		cnEcCreateDirectoryA, and added a new function called cnEcCreateDirectoryW.
		
		Renamed the cnEcCreateFile External Function as	cnEcCreateFileA,	cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		and added a new function called cnEcCreateFileW.
		
		Renamed the cnEcGetFileAttributes External Function as				cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		cnEcGetFileAttributesA, and added a new function called cnEcGetFileAttributesW.
		
		Renamed the cnEcMoveFile External Function as cnEcMoveFileA,		cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		and added a new function called cnEcMoveFileW.
		
		Renamed the cnEcRemoveDirectory External Function as				cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		cnEcRemoveDirectoryA, and added a new function called cnEcRemoveDirectoryW.
		
		Changed access to the following properties on the CnEcArrayObject	cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		class to read-only:
		
			o binaryValue
			o stringValue
		
		Added the CnEcWildcardSearch class for searching strings using		cnwdad1 21/01/2002
		wildcard patterns.
		
		Added the following methods to the FileNode class:					cnwdad1 22/01/2002
		
			o cnEcIsFile(): Boolean;
			o cnEcIsFolder(): Boolean;
		
		Both methods return a false value, however the cnEcIsFile method is reimplemented on
		the File class to return true, and cnEcIsFolder is reimplemented on the FileFolder
		class to return true.
		
		Added the CnEcFileFolder and CnEcFolderSearch classes.				cnwdad1 22/01/2002
		
		Added the following method to the Integer Primitive:				cnwdad1 22/01/2002
		
			o cnEcClockDifference():Real;
		
		This method will return the difference between the receiver and the app.clock value,
		in seconds.
		
		Made the following changes to the CnEcDateRange class:				cnwdad1 28/01/2002
		
			o Added constructor and destructor methods to create and delete the from
			  and to date references.
			
			o Changed the updateMe() method to accept primitives rather than date objects.
		
		Made the following changes to the CnEcCurrencyRange class:			cnwdad1 28/01/2002
		
			o Added constructor and destructor methods to create and delete the from
			  and to currency references.
			
			o Changed the updateMe() method to accept (Real) primitives rather than currency objects.
		
		Added the CnEcColor class.											cnwndl1 29/01/2002
		
		Added the App::cnEcMaybe() method.									cnwdad1 29/01/2002
		
		Renamed the CnEcXMLParser class as CnEcXmlParser.					cnwdad1 15/02/2002
		
		Modified the CnEcXmlStructureInstance::initializeMe method to no	cnwdad1 21/02/2002
		longer set the tagData property.  Instead, the property will now only be set by a
		reimplementation of the initializeMe method on the CnEcXmlFieldInstance subclass.

==========================================================================================
2.5.03	Changed the CnEcXMLClassFormatMaint::sampleClick method to check	cnwdad1 07/03/2002
		whether the Class being used for the sample was found, and also whether an
		instance of that class exists.  If either check fails, then an error message
		dialog (message box) is displayed.
		
		Fixed the CnEcCurrencyBox and CnEcNumericBox custom controls.		cnwdad1 12/03/2002
		The lostFocus event was supposed to convert the contents of the textboxes into a
		currency or numeric format, but this was not being done correctly (the value was
		being formatted as a plain numeric value instead).
		
		Fixed the CnEcCurrencyBox and CnEcNumericBox custom controls.		cnwdad1 13/03/2002
		The "text" mapping method wasn't checking whether the CurrencyFormat or the
		Numeric Format reference was set, which resulted in 1090 exceptions within
		the Painter.  Also added checks in the "gotFocus" event methods for a selecton
		style of "All" - if this option is set, then the contents will be selected
		after the newly formatted contents are set.  This is necessary because we're
		switching from an alphanumeric textbox to a numeric textbox.
		
		Changed the Class::cnEcGetImplementationSchema() method to now use	cnwdad1 27/03/2002
		the Type::rootType() method (much more efficient).
		
		Patched the CnEcRateGraphDriver class and associated External		cnwdad1 05/04/2002
		Functions to correct a problem where the X and Y Axis text was not being
		correctly drawn for a thin client node.
		
		Added the following method to the Date Primitive:					cnwdad1 09/04/2002
		
			o cnEcDaysInYear():Integer;
		
		Added the following method to the Integer Primitive:				cnwdad1 09/04/2002
		
			o cnEcIsBetween(pLowerValue:Integer; pUpperValue:Integer):Boolean;
		
		Added the following methods to the Global class:					cnwdad1 09/04/2002
		
			o cnEcSoundexIndigenousAustralia(pName:String):String;
			o cnEcValidateMedicareNumber(pCardNumber:String):Boolean;
	
	Changed the app.cnEcNotImplemented method to fetch the second element	cnwdad1 22/04/2002
	of the call stack instead of the first.</text>
